            In the course of earlier debates, the Government indicated that they will look favourably on an amendment to bring in a clearance procedure. At Second Reading, the noble Baroness, on behalf of the Government, said that the regulator would be able to issue a contribution notice under Clause 35 only where an act or failure to act was deliberate and designed to avoid pension liabilities and that the regulator would be able to issue financial support directions only in prescribed circumstances. I shall not burden the Committee with the exact quotation.</p><p>
